┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ OVERVIEW                                                                        │
│                                                                                 │
│ A quasiperfect number N satisfies σ(N) = 2N + 1.  Such N must be an odd        │
│ perfect square (Cattaneo 1951).  We write N = ∏ p_i^{2e_i}, decompose          │
│ N = N_L · N_R² where N_L encodes the "left prefix" (small primes with          │
│ known exponents) and N_R encodes the "right suffix" (unknown).  Then:          │
│                                                                                 │
│   σ(N_L) · σ(N_R²) = 2 · N_L · N_R² + 1                                      │
│                                                                                 │
│ The engine constructs all feasible N_L prefixes via DFS, then for each          │
│ prefix, solves a modular congruence (ray-casting) to find candidate N_R         │
│ values and checks whether σ(z²) matches the required value.                    │
│                                                                                 │
│ PRIOR RESULT: No QPN exists below 10^35 (Hagis 1980 / Cohen 2015).            │
│ THIS RUN:     Verifies no QPN exists in the range 10^35 < N < 10^37.           │
│                                                                                 │
│ SUBSYSTEMS:                                                                     │
│   Phase 0 — Lean 4 Build & Formal Proof Verification                           │
│   Phase 1 — Legendre-Cattaneo Sieve (cyclotomic mod-8 screening)               │
│   Phase 2 — Fused DFS Construction & Ray-Casting (with Z3 CDCL pruning)        │
│                                                                                 │
│ The Lean 4 proofs establish the mathematical foundations:                        │
│   • qpn_is_odd_square:          N must be an odd perfect square                │
│   • legendre_cattaneo_obstruction: All σ(p^{2e}) prime factors ≡ 1,3 (mod 8)  │
│   • qpn_coprime_15_omega_15:    gcd(N,15)=1 ⟹ ω(N) ≥ 15                     │
│   • abundancy_starvation:        Running abundancy bound for feasibility       │
│   • zsigmondy_poison_trap:       Zsigmondy cyclotomic divisibility trap        │
│   • correction_factor_bound:     Totient ratio threshold for pruning           │
│   • sigma_prime_pow_cyclotomic:  σ(p^k) = ∏ Φ_d(p) for d | (k+1)             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


